news.title: Mysuru development body stops inviting applications from site seekers
news.para: Sometime back, the number of applicants seeking sites from the urban development body was around 80,000 and authorities had been promising to provide them sites.

news.title: Nashik civic body plans GIS mapping of entire city
news.para: The digital mapping of all the city roads, properties, green and yellow areas of the city along with underground drainage lines, piped gas lines and various ducts have been planned by the civic body.

news.title: Jaipur development body to sell seized plots to build colonies
news.para: After auctioning these plots, the civic body will complete the development work in these colonies. The move will benefit lakhs of people who were deprived of basic facilities including roads, sewerage, parks after purchasing plots from private developers.

news.title: Gurugram: Give us a proper place to stay, say residents of Chintels Paradiso tower
news.para: The residents have been staying with their friends or relatives since February 10, when the floors caved in. On Sunday, the flat owners gheraoed an official of developer Chintels who visited Paradiso in the morning.

news.title: Take stringent action against Chintels Paradiso's builder, if not, will intensify protest: RWAs
news.para: The representatives of 50 housing societies have lent their support to the residents of Chintels Paradiso who have been rendered homeless after a vertical collapse of the living rooms of five flats from the sixth to the first floors in one of the towers.

news.title: Redevelopment benefit linked to area, not income: Bombay HC
news.para: At least 48 old buildings are being redeveloped in Samata Nagar. The six occupants said their building is in the middle-income group (MIG) category but they occupy 18sqm tenements.

news.title: Will tweak policy for granting OCs to buildings: Haryana deputy CM
news.para: Currently, the department of town and country planning (DTCP) issues an OC to a developer after checking if the building has been constructed in keeping with the approved layout plan and the Haryana Building Code. There is no provision to check the quality of construction at the time of granting the OC.

news.title: Hines plans India-dedicated fund to invest in office properties
news.para: The US-based firm is planning to raise the India-dedicated fund worth $500 million in the next two quarters as part of its growth strategy. This will be a close-ended fund with a total tenure of 10 years.

news.title: Flats yet to be delivered seven years on, Mayfair Residency buyers stage protest
news.para: Most of the buyers had invested in the project in 2011 and were promised delivery of their flats in 2015. However, seven years down the line, close to 600 families still await possession of their flats in the society that has a total of 1,054 flats spread across 12 towers.

news.title: MahaRERA directs Prathamesh Harmony's promoter to hand over flats in four months
news.para: MahaRERA member Vijay Satbir Singh, in his order, also stated that the society would be entitled to take over this project if promoter Ajit Singh failed to complete it by obtaining an occupancy certificate (OC).

news.title: Second FIR lodged in sequential fall of flat roofs in Chintels Paradiso
news.para: ​The incident involving the sequential collapse of flat roofs from the sixth to ground floor in the 18-storied tower of the Chintel Paradiso Housing Complex in sector 109 of Gurugram on Thursday had led to the killing of two women living in two lower floor flats died and critical injuries to a man.

news.title: Godrej Properties plans Rs 7,500 crore investment in next 12-18 months
news.para: "We will invest USD 1 billion (around Rs 7,500 crore) over the next 12-18 months on development of new projects," Godrej Executive Chairman Pirojsha Godrej said, adding that the planned investments would be in mix of equity and debt.

news.title: Vadodara civic body claims its coffers have got richer due to building permissions
news.para: It has come to light that in 2018-19 VMC received Rs 188.48crore towards charges for building construction permissions. In 2019-20, the amount was Rs 192.96 crore and Rs 179.77crore in 2020-21.

news.title: Gurugram: Brisk Lumbini residents file complaint about poor construction quality
news.para: In their complaint, the residents alleged they had earlier raised concern about plaster chunks falling from balconies, cracks in pillars and seepage in the basement but no attention had been paid to it.

news.title: Rajasthan budget may not allocate funds for Jaipur Metro phase-II
news.para: Many believe, the government should consider Metro on Tonk Road as corridor which runs from South to North and connects all major areas.
